I have python code that generates one .docx file, and I need to check where are soft page breaks and hard page breaks. I use this script:

```python
import docx

document= docx.Document('REPORT.docx')

for p in document.paragraphs:
    for run in p.runs:
        if 'lastRenderedPageBreak' in run._element.xml:
            print 'soft page break found at run:', run.text
        if 'w:br' in run._element.xml and 'type="page"' in run._element.xml:
            print 'hard page break found at run:', run.text
```

The problem is when I read the generated document immediately after it's created, the printed result from the code above is not correct(number of soft page breaks is lower than real soft page breaks in the document). But if I manually open the REPORT.docx, type in one single letter and after that delete it and save the document(Actually there is nothing changed in it), when executing the script again the number of soft page breaks now is correct. I also noticed that file size is getting bigger after this.

Can someone explain why is this happening? I want to check when insert image, is it on the same page or (if it's too large) is automatically moved to the next page when generating REPORT.docx file. So if there is another way to do that, please tell me.

